### Test Mini Practices API
### This file can be used with REST Client extension in VS Code

### Health Check
GET http://localhost:5001/api/health

###

### Get All Mini Practices
GET http://localhost:5001/api/mini-practices

###

### Get Practice by ID (with System Prompt)
GET http://localhost:5001/api/mini-practices/1

###

### Get Practice by ID #2
GET http://localhost:5001/api/mini-practices/2

###

### Get All Categories
GET http://localhost:5001/api/mini-practices/meta/categories

###

### Get Practices by Category
GET http://localhost:5001/api/mini-practices/category/Communication%20Skills

###

### Search Practices
GET http://localhost:5001/api/mini-practices/search?q=conversation

###

### Create New Practice
POST http://localhost:5001/api/mini-practices
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Active Listening",
  "description": "Practice the art of active listening by asking follow-up questions that show genuine interest and understanding.",
  "tags": ["intermediate", "listening", "empathy"],
  "category": "Communication Skills",
  "systemPrompt": "You are a coach teaching active listening skills. Guide students to ask questions that demonstrate they're truly hearing and understanding the other person's experience."
}

###

### Update Practice
PUT http://localhost:5001/api/mini-practices/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Conversation Basics - Updated",
  "description": "Master the art of turning closed questions into engaging open-ended conversations. Now with more examples!"
}

###

### Delete Practice (be careful!)
# DELETE http://localhost:5001/api/mini-practices/3

###

### Generate Practice Question (using practice 1's system prompt)
POST http://localhost:5001/api/practice/generate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "systemPrompt": "Get this from GET /api/mini-practices/1"
}
